title: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau to meet U.S. President Donald Trump Monday
text: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau to meet U.S. President Donald Trump Monday While the two leaders have spoken by telephone several times, this will be their first face-to-face meeting. Prime Minister Justin Trudeau will travel to Washington Monday to meet with U.S. President Donald Trump. ( Adrian Wyld / THE CANADIAN PRESS ) By Bruce Campion-Smith Ottawa Bureau Thu., Feb. 9, 2017 OTTAWA—Prime Minister Justin Trudeau will travel to Washington Monday to meet with U.S. President Donald Trump. “They look forward to discussing ‎the unique relationship between Canada and the United States of America and how we can continue to work hard for middle class Canadians and Americans, together,” Kate Purchase, Trudeau’s director of communications, said in a statement. While the two leaders have spoken by telephone several times, this will be their first face-to-face meeting. The meeting comes after several cabinet meetings have made their own trips to Washington this week to meet with their U.S. counterparts and forge relations with the new Trump administration. More to come
